Package: BayesMuCoSoT
Type: Package
Title: Multivariate Bayesian Modeling for Common Source Testing
Version: 1.1.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Lampis",
           family = "Tzai", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email="lampi.tzai@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
           )
Description: Bayesian multivariate normal modelling (family Normal-inverse-Wishart) for common source testing. This library can help you to test if two multivariate data distribution comes from the same source based on logarithmic Bayes factor. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Details: To run you have to install Jags Bayesian software from https://sourceforge.net/projects/mcmc-jags/
